the ability to deliver into this area an aggregate of over 70 MMcf/d.  If we=
 do see firm and interruptible gas nominated into these points in excess of =
this amount, I feel Northern Border must zero out the interruptibles on our =
side - that was the issue that created so much heart burn for Pan Alberta ye=
ars ago when we were forced to allocate Ventura.  But that is as far as we a=
re planning to go.   We view the flow restriction to be on your side.  And w=
e are suggesting that your priorities be used to allocate Aberdeen on the 1s=
t.=20
